                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18471122-244-offence-1 t18471122-name-1353"></join>John Hough</persName>, fixed to a building; and </rs>
                  <persName id="def3-244-18471122" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def3-244-18471122" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def3-244-18471122" type="age" value="27"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def3-244-18471122" type="surname" value="HYMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def3-244-18471122" type="given" value="DAVID"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">DAVID HYMAN</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18471122-244-offence-2" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18471122-244-offence-2" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18471122-244-offence-2" type="offenceSubcategory" value="receiving"></interp>, feloniously receiving the same.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">WALKER</hi> pleaded <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18471122-244-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18471122-244-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-244-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>.</hi> Aged 13.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">MOORE</hi> pleaded <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18471122-244-verdict-2" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18471122-244-verdict-2" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-244-verdict-2" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>.</hi> Aged 11.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">
                     <rs id="t18471122-244-punishment-208" type="punishmentDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18471122-244-punishment-208" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-244-punishment-208" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>
                        <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-244-18471122 t18471122-244-punishment-208"></join>
                        <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="def2-244-18471122 t18471122-244-punishment-208"></join>Confined Three Months</rs>.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18471122-name-1355" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1355" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1355" type="surname" value="RICE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1355" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY RICE.</persName>
                  </hi> On Saturday, 6th Nov., I went with Walker and Moore to 3, Peckham-grove—we took a copper out, took it to one place, and they would not buy it—we took it to Hyman—he bought it for 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. O'BRIEN.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What time was it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Between six and seven in the evening.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18471122-name-1356" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1356" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1356" type="surname" value="QUINNEAR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1356" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE QUINNEAR</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman</hi>, 201 <hi rend="italic">P.</hi>) I took Walker—he pointed out Hyman's shop to me—Hyman was there, and Walker said, "That is the person I sold the cooper to on Saturday night, and the cooper I had on Friday I sold to the woman"—Hyman and his wife were both present—Hyman</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184711220225"></xptr>
               <p>said, "I can assure you, policeman, it is false; I bought nothing of the kind"—Walker said, "We asked six shillings for it; you weighed it, and gave us 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> ✗ copper he referred to belonged to Mr. Hadlow? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> He referred to two the copper he sold on Saturday evening to Hyman belonged to ✗ugh—it was the copper taken on Saturday, 6th Nov.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18471122-name-1357" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1357" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1357" type="surname" value="RICE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1357" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH RICE.</persName>
                  </hi> I went to Hyman's shop on Saturday night, 6th Nov.—I said, "I understand my little boy has brought a copper here; you should not buy anything from these children unless their parents know it; you should inquire of the parents"—he came out from his shop—I said, "This is a very serious thing"—he said, "You keep your boy in away from the other boys, it will soon blow over."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18471122-name-1358" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1358" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1358" type="surname" value="NASH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1358" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES NASH.</persName>
                  </hi> I am coachman to Mr. John Hough—he has an empty house at 3, Peckham-grove—I saw a copper safe there at five o'clock in the evening of 6th Nov.—I missed it about eight o'clock the same evening.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18471122-name-1359" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1359" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1359" type="surname" value="HADLOW"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1359" type="given" value="SAMUEL JOSEPH"></interp>SAMUEL JOSEPH HADLOW.</persName>
                  </hi> On 8th Nov. I went to Hyman's shop—I said, "Have you had a copper brought here, and other things, "which I described, "for sale"—he said, "No"—I said, "I have had a house broken into, and these things stolen"—he said he knew nothing of them—I described the copper to him—I was standing looking at his stall a few days afterwards, and he said to me, "Have you heard of your copper, Sir?"—I said, "No, I have not indeed"—after a moment's pause, he said, "All these things you know make good for trade."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Had he known you before? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I had bought a stove of him two or three weeks before—I am not in business now—I was a stockbroker for many years—I dealt in stock about a month ago—I know what they mean by <hi rend="italic">a lame duck</hi>—I believe it was never said of me that I was the most notorious liar in the Stock Exchange—I never heard it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you ever sell your copper to Mr. Hyman? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—my character is quite different to a most notorious liar—I can bring 100 witnesses to my character.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18471122-name-1360" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1360" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1360" type="surname" value="FRY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1360" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY FRY.</persName>
                  </hi> The boys, Walker and Rice, came to me with a cooper on 6th Nov.—I refused to buy it—my place is about five minutes' walk from Hyam's.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> They told you it belonged to their father? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. O'BRIEN</hi> to <hi rend="smallCaps">HENRY RICE.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What time did you sell the copper to Hyman? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> We took it between five and six o'clock, took it to Fry's about seven, and sold it to Hyman about eight.</p>
               <p>(Hyman received a good character,)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">HYMAN</hi>—
<rs id="t18471122-244-verdict-3" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18471122-244-verdict-3" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18471122-244-verdict-3" type="verdictSubcategory" value="withRecommendation"></interp>
                     <hi rend="smallCaps">GUILTY.</hi> Aged 27.—<hi rend="italic">Recommended to mercy by the Jury.</hi>
                  </rs>
